x4freetext: ND2007 report
Ref. for Subents 002-004.
The 150 MeV Geel Electron Linac,
GELINA. Electron beam (800 Hz) accelerated to 150 MeV.
DC440 digitizers from Acquiris - 12 bits amplitude
resolution, 4096 channels full range, sampling
frequency of 420 Msamples/s, 2.38 ns/sample.
Neutron produced via U-238(g,xn) and U-238(g,f)
reactions as result of bremsstrahlung.
Thick rotary U-238 target.
current of 70 microA.
Direct neutron flux has a mixed evaporation and
fission neutron spectrum, extended from 0.1 MeV to
about 20 MeV.
Time-of-flight technique with a 200 m flight path.
8 nsec time-of-flight resolution for 1-MeV neutrons.
An Al frame was installed for twelve HPGe
detectors. Four detectors may be supported at each of
110, 125 and 150 deg angles. First eight detectors were
currently placed at 110 and 150 deg -four in horizontal
and four in vertical plane. Seven detectors have
relative efficiency of 100 % and one - 70%.
Detection efficiency was measured with Eu152 point
source.
Also MCNP simulations to determine efficiency
corresponding to the extended dimensions of sample.
U-235 fission chamber at 200 m cabin - to
monitor neutron flux, for absolute normalization.
All measurements relative to
U-235 fission cross-sections.
-For neutron multiple scattering and gamma absorption
via MCNP simulations.
Approved by author A.Negret 09.02.2015.
M.M.

x4freetext: Correlation ( between energy points) matrix for total
inelastic cross section is on Fig.2 of
Uncertainties introducing correlations between various
cross sections determined in this experiment:
Uncertainty from the activity of the source
used for efficiency calibration of the HPGe detectors:
0.7%; common for all detectors;
Uncertainty from the beam monitoring with the
fission chamber - 1.5 %.
The statistical uncertainty of the HPGe data is
of the order of 2% for each detector for the strongest
neutron energy channels. This is reduced by the fact
that eight detectors were used. Further, if the
statistical uncertainty remains too high, authors group
a few time channels adding the statistics and
sacrificing time resolution.
Total uncertainty includes all sources of
errors for the strongest channels - 5-6% .
Of author.
The total cross section is precise up to the energy of
the last observed level. Beyond this energy it
represents only a lower limit of the real inelastic
cross section. However, this limit is very close to the
real value because most of the gamma decay of 56Fe
proceeds through the first excited level 846.8 keV, 2+
and the decay of this level is clearly observed.
Data were received from the author A.Negret.
Data are on Fig.11 of PR/C,90,034602,2014.
Preliminary data are presented on Fig.3 of
2007NICE in energy range from about 1 MeV to about
18 MeV.
M.M.

Level density calculated by BSFG model.
The level densities are compared with
theoretical values calculated on base of back-shifted
Fermi gas (BSFG) model with only two free parameters,
the level density parameter and the excitation energy
shift, using the approach described in REL-REF JP/CS
with the parameters determined in REL-REF PR/C.
The angular momenta of the states populated in the
compound nucleus in the 56Fe(n,inl) reaction were
determined using the TALYS 1.6 calculations.
